        </div>

        <h3>2. Industry-specific stack for a dental practice</h3>
        <p>Beyond the foundation 15, a dentist adds: Healthgrades, Zocdoc, Vitals, RateMDs, WebMD Provider Directory, ADA Find-a-Dentist. Each carries higher relevance weight than a generic aggregator listing.</p>

        <h3>3. Fixing 200 inconsistent legacy citations</h3>
        <p>A regional business chain moved office in 2023 but never updated legacy citations. 200 old-address listings were fixed via a citation cleanup engagement — Local Pack visibility for city queries recovered within 8 weeks of the cleanup.</p>

        <h2 id="vs-related">Citation vs backlink — how they differ</h2>
        <p>Both are external references to your business, but they serve different SEO systems.</p>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros-card">
            <h4>Citation</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Mentions NAP data, may or may not link</li>
              <li>Serves local SEO (Local Pack ranking)</li>
              <li>Value comes from data consistency + directory quality</li>
              <li>Verifies business legitimacy to Google</li>
              <li>Ideal target: 80-150 per business</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons-card">
            <h4>Backlink</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Hyperlink from another site to yours</li>
              <li>Serves organic rankings (PageRank flow)</li>
              <li>Value comes from linking domain authority + anchor text</li>
              <li>Signals topical relevance and trust</li>
              <li>No universal target — quality over quantity</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="best-practices">6 best practices for citation building</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Submit to the four major data aggregators first.</strong> One submission cascades to hundreds of downstream directories. Highest-ROI single action.</li>
          <li><strong>Build 50 structured citations manually.</strong> Yelp, BBB, YellowPages, industry directories, chamber of commerce. Manual submission avoids the risk of automated tools introducing NAP inconsistency.</li>
          <li><strong>Maintain exact NAP formatting.</strong> Same name spelling, same address format, same phone punctuation across every listing. Formatting variations are a common cause of consistency loss.</li>
          <li><strong>Run quarterly citation audits.</strong> BrightLocal, Whitespark, or Moz Local can scan hundreds of directories and flag inconsistencies or duplicates.</li>
          <li><strong>Prioritise quality over quantity.</strong> 50 accurate citations on authoritative directories outperform 200 inconsistent citations on low-quality sites. A citation on a Chamber page beats a citation on an auto-scraped aggregator.</li>
          <li><strong>Complement with fresh GBP content.</strong> Citation signals interact with Google Business Profile activity. Regular GBP posts, photos, and Q&amp;A updates amplify the citation lift.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">Common mistake — chasing 500 low-quality citations</div>
          <p>Automated citation-blast services can dump your business on 500 auto-generated directories in a week. Google's algorithms recognise this pattern and discount those citations heavily. 50 accurate citations on real directories will outperform 500 spammy ones — often dramatically.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="mistakes">Common citation mistakes to avoid</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Inconsistent NAP formatting</strong> — "Street" vs "St." vs "St" across listings</li>
          <li><strong>Ignoring data aggregators</strong> — one bad aggregator entry poisons hundreds of downstream sites</li>
          <li><strong>Letting duplicate listings persist</strong> — two Yelp entries for the same business signal chaos to Google</li>
          <li><strong>Skipping industry-specific directories</strong> — a dentist without Zocdoc is missing a vertical-relevance signal</li>
          <li><strong>Forgetting to update citations after moving</strong> — legacy addresses linger for years without proactive cleanup</li>
          <li><strong>Treating citations as one-time work</strong> — directories update policies, close, or drop listings continuously</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="how-thestacc-helps">How theStacc helps with citations</h2>
        <p>theStacc automates the full citation stack: submissions to the four major data aggregators, manual building on the foundation 15 directories, industry-specific and geo-specific outreach, and quarterly consistency audits. The platform pairs citation building with automated GBP posts (up to 80 per month), local landing pages, and blog content — the full Local Pack ranking flywheel in one workflow.</p>

